Less than 72 hours after the Federal Government granted financial autonomy to local governments in Nigeria, lawmakers in Imo State on Thursday suspended all the elected chairmen of the 27 Local Government Areas of the state. The action of the lawmakers followed the refusal of the chairmen to appear before the house to answer questions on the financial standing of their respective local governments. Member representing Nkwerre state constituency, Chika Madumere, moved the motion for the immediate suspension of the chairmen, a motion that and was unanimously supported by all the lawmakers seated at the plenary. According to him, by failing to appear before the lawmakers, the chairmen exhibited lack of respect for, and also undermined the legislature. Zamfara Assembly extends tenure of LG chairmen PDP, LG chairmen allege witch-hunt, intimidation in planned public hearing by Ekiti assembly Benue Assembly suspends 6 council chairmen Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin